            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Because the neovim experience will differ wildly between different distributions and systems which is not desirable for users who expect a consistent behavior. Even if the user can override these, they'll still end up with changed defaults they might dislike and have to spend time to figure out which system file causes the change and what they need to fix in their config.\r\n\r\nAlso a perfectly reasonable workaround has been provided: call lua file from `sysinit.vim` or run lua code directly in `sysinit.vim`, so I'm not sure what the problem is here.",
